	Executive summary excerpt: "Five years post-implementation, the 2025 Biodiversity Accords show surprising success in unexpected areas. While protected area targets lagged at 68% achievement, the 'Neighbor Forest' initiative—where nations adopt adjacent countries' endangered species—led to grassroots conservation movements that exceeded all projections. Costa Rica's protection of Panama's golden frogs sparked a phenomenon."
