	"The Riverside Community's fight against toxic waste disposal revealed a new model of environmental justice that transcends traditional boundaries. When contamination threatened the local river, the community didn't just protest—they purchased the upstream woodland using a community land trust. Five years later, the aquifer is recovering and the community operates a profitable maple syrup cooperative."
