	Best practices guide: "'Council of All Beings' sessions, adapted from Joanna Macy's work, transformed Brookfield's watershed planning. Residents role-played as river, eagle, and wetland. While some officials initially balked, the resulting watershed protection plan—incorporating these 'non-human' perspectives—passed with 94% public approval and successfully defended against three lawsuits."
